vulnerability.name: USN-4100-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that KConfig and KDE libraries have a vulnerability where an attacker could hide malicious code under desktop and configuration files. (CVE-2019-14744)  It was discovered that KConfig allows remote attackers to write to arbitrary files via a ../ in a filename in an archive file. (CVE-2016-6232)

statements.status_notes: KConfig and KDE libraries could be made to crash or run programs if it opened a specially crafted file.
